      "content": "thanks. the smart pointers might be a bit heavy for this specific micro, so i'd rather stick to manual management if possible. \n\nthe `remove_oldest()` call definitely looks suspicious. i looked at the implementation and it seems to be popping the pointer from the container, but it doesn't actually call `delete` on the object itself. that's a huge oversight on my part. i'll fix that.\n\nbut even with that fix, i'm still worried about other places where we might be losing track of pointers. since i can't use Valgrind, what's a good way to \"trap\" these leaks in real-time without tanking the CPU performance? like, is there a way to build a lightweight wrapper or a custom allocator that can alert me when something isn't being accounted for?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
